<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<ScrollView xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:app="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res-auto"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    tools:context=".YogaInfo">

    <RelativeLayout
        android:layout_width="match_parent"
        android:layout_height="match_parent">
        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/text1"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="90dp"
            android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
            android:paddingLeft="20dp"
            android:fontFamily="@font/amaranth"
            android:paddingRight="50dp"
            android:text="Yoga asanas for stress relief: These 5 yoga poses will help reduce stress and anxiety"
            android:textSize="20sp"
            android:textStyle="bold" />

        <ImageView
            android:id="@+id/imageView2"
            android:layout_width="211dp"
            android:layout_height="128dp"

            android:layout_marginTop="150dp"
            android:layout_marginLeft="80dp"/>

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/text2"
            android:layout_width="399dp"
            android:layout_height="110dp"
            android:layout_below="@+id/imageView2"
            android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
            android:fontFamily="@font/amaranth"
            android:textSize="18sp"
            android:text="1. Sukhasana (Easy pose)
Sukhasana will lengthen your spine and open your hips. It will help you calm down and eliminate anxiety. It will also reduce mental and physical exhaustion" />

        <ImageView
            android:id="@+id/imageView3"
            android:layout_width="211dp"
            android:layout_height="128dp"
            android:layout_below="@+id/text2"

            android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
            android:layout_marginLeft="80dp"/>

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/text3"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="100dp"
            android:layout_below="@+id/imageView3"
            android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
            android:textSize="20sp"
            android:fontFamily="@font/amaranth"
            android:text="2. Balasana (Childâ€™s pose)
Balasana is beneficial for your lymphatic system and nervous system. It will calm your mind and release stress."/>

        <ImageView
            android:id="@+id/imageView4"
            android:layout_width="211dp"
            android:layout_height="128dp"
            android:layout_below="@+id/text3"

            android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
            android:layout_marginLeft="80dp"/>

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/text4"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="120dp"
            android:layout_below="@+id/imageView4"
            android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
            android:textSize="20sp"
            android:fontFamily="@font/amaranth"
            android:text="3. Paschimottanasana (Seated forward bend)
Paschimottanasana will stretch your spine, hamstring and lower back. Apart from relieving stress, this pose will ease the symptoms of PMS, improves digestion, stimulated liver, reduce fatigue and relieves symptoms of menopause."/>

        <ImageView
            android:id="@+id/imageView5"
            android:layout_width="211dp"
            android:layout_height="128dp"
            android:layout_below="@+id/text4"

            android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
            android:layout_marginLeft="80dp"/>

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/text5"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="110dp"
            android:layout_below="@+id/imageView5"
            android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
            android:textSize="20sp"
            android:fontFamily="@font/amaranth"
            android:text="4. Ananda Balasana (Happy baby pose)
Ananda Balasana will help calm you and get rid of fatigue and stress. It will gently stretch your spine and groin."/>

        <ImageView
            android:id="@+id/imageView6"
            android:layout_width="211dp"
            android:layout_height="128dp"
            android:layout_below="@+id/text5"

            android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
            android:layout_marginLeft="80dp"/>

        <TextView
            android:id="@+id/text6"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="115dp"
            android:layout_below="@+id/imageView6"
            android:layout_marginTop="20dp"
            android:fontFamily="@font/amaranth"
            android:textSize="18sp"
            android:text="5. Uttanasana (Standing forward bend)
Uttanasana will relieve mild depression and stress. It will calm your brain and stimulate your kidneys and liver. It will also strengthen your knees and stretch your hips, calves and hamstring."/>
    </RelativeLayout>



</ScrollView>